<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

External Connect lets external tools (Claude Code, scripts, LLMs) push tiddlers into the wiki via CLI import — no running server needed. A shared resolution pipeline with context-aware rules and profile-based templates transforms raw JSON into fully-formed tiddlers with optional post-creation actions.

* ''Inbound'' — CLI import (`--import`) is the primary path. External tools write a JSON file and run the CLI command; the deserializer resolves context, evaluates templates, writes `.tid` files to disk, and exits. A fallback POST endpoint exists for live-server scenarios but may be deprecated.
* ''Outbound'' — `@Target` commands in tiddler text are extracted into separate command tiddlers routed to a watched folder on disk. External tools monitor that folder and process commands without watching the entire wiki.

!! Features

!!! Inbound (push)

* ''CLI import'' — primary path: `TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1 npx tiddlywiki mywiki --import input.json application/x-rimir-ext-connect`
* ''Context resolution'' — caller specifies context tiddlers; their fields are available as variables in template filter expressions and rule matching
* ''Profiles'' — named mappings to template tiddlers (e.g. "meeting-note" → template with title prefix + tags)
* ''Rule-based dispatch'' — ordered rules use TW filter expressions to match context; first match selects template tiddler(s)
* ''Template tiddlers'' — fields are TW filter expressions; `out.` prefix for reserved field names; `text` field runs as post-creation actions
* ''Post-creation actions'' — template `text` field contains action widgets executed server-side after tiddler creation
* ''Auto-persist'' — CLI path writes `.tid` files directly; server path uses syncer
* ''Fallback: POST API'' — `POST /api/ext-connect/put-tiddler` for live-server integration (may be deprecated)

!!! Outbound (text-commands)

* ''`@Target` extraction'' — write `@LLM summarize this` in a tiddler, save, and the command is extracted into a separate tiddler
* ''Multi-line commands'' — `@Target` ... `Target@` block syntax for longer commands
* ''Configurable targets'' — JSON array of registered target names (e.g. `["LLM", "Dodo"]`)
* ''Scan filter'' — only tiddlers matching a configurable filter are scanned (e.g. `[tag[process]]`)
* ''FileSystemPaths routing'' — extracted command tiddlers are tagged and routed to `tiddlers/ext-outbox/` on disk
* ''Inline transclusion'' — original text is replaced with a live-updating view of command status

!! Prerequisites

* TiddlyWiki installed via npm (Node.js)
* Set `TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1` for CLI import (prevents filesystem-watcher from keeping the process alive)

!! Quick start

# Create an input JSON file:

```json
{"text": "Hello from external"}
```

# Run the CLI import:

```
TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1 npx tiddlywiki mywiki --import input.json application/x-rimir-ext-connect
```

# The tiddler appears at `Inbox/<timestamp>` with the `Inbox` tag (from the `default` profile template)

# Use a profile for different defaults:

```json
{"text": "Meeting notes", "profile": "meeting-note"}
```

# Use context for rule-based dispatch (with post-creation actions):

```json
{"text": "Reply content", "context": ["MyStreamTiddler"]}
```

